Task: Fully implement all sub-tabs in the Environments view with interactive state-driven content.
вЂ‹1. State Management for Tabs:
вЂ‹Implement a useState hook to track the active sub-tab.
вЂ‹Use a switch statement or a mapping object to render different content based on the active tab.
вЂ‹2. Tab-by-Tab Implementation (Strict Adherence):
вЂ‹General: Show a two-column "Environment Details" card. Left: Name, ID, IP, Region (with copy icons). Right: Technical Specs (PHP Version, Disk Usage, SSL Status).
вЂ‹Pods & Nodes: Build a high-density table.
вЂ‹Columns: Name, Status (Pulsing Dot), CPU (Dynamic %), RAM (Dynamic %), Restart (Button).
вЂ‹Logic: Use setInterval to make CPU/RAM fluctuate between 10% and 80%.
вЂ‹Deployments (The Core Flow):
вЂ‹Deployment Card: Create the 4-step sequential form: Pipeline -> Provider -> Repository -> Branch.
вЂ‹Functional Lock: Dropdown n+1 must be disabled unless dropdown n has a value.
вЂ‹Tasks Table: List recent deployments with a progress bar for the top one.
вЂ‹Firewall:
вЂ‹Table of whitelisted IPs.
вЂ‹"Add IP" form with a "Use My Current IP" button.
